COVID-19 Status 💉 🦠

As of 11:55AM PT today, over 1.5 million Canadians have tested positive for COVID-19. Sadly, 26.8 thousand have died.

In the last day, 1.5 thousand new infections were reported and 4 deaths. This is trending upwards.

Fortunately, 52.2 million doses of the vaccine have been administered. For those 12 years and older, 82.7% have their 1st shot and 73.8% are fully vaccinated!

Vaccination is slowing down, but there are 11.3 million doses in the freezer. It currently takes ~89 days for new deliveries to get into arms.

At the current rate, Canadians should achieve herd immunity around Dec-23 when 80% of the entire population is fully vaccinated. There is no approved vaccine for children aged 11 or younger.
